        <content type="html"><![CDATA[<h2 id="Terms"><a href="#Terms" class="headerlink" title="Terms"></a>Terms</h2><p>resident set size (RSS)</p><h2 id="Comands"><a href="#Comands" class="headerlink" title="Comands"></a>Comands</h2><h2 id="File"><a href="#File" class="headerlink" title="File"></a>File</h2><p>&#x2F;proc&#x2F;self&#x2F;statm</p><h3 id="top"><a href="#top" class="headerlink" title="top"></a>top</h3><h4 id="Fields"><a href="#Fields" class="headerlink" title="Fields"></a>Fields</h4><table><thead><tr><th>TIME+<sup><a href="%5Bwhat-does-time-cpu-time-hundredth-in-top-mean%5D(https://superuser.com/questions/1148884/what-does-time-cpu-time-hundredth-in-top-mean/)">1</a></sup></th><th>TIME</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><code>5432:01</code> means “5432 minutes and 1 second”</td><td><code>90,32</code> means “90 hours and 32 minutes”</td></tr><tr><td><code>25:15.20</code> means “25 minutes, 15 seconds and 20% of 1 second”</td><td><code>25:15</code> means “25 minutes and 15 seconds”</td></tr></tbody></table><h3 id="ps"><a href="#ps" class="headerlink" title="ps"></a>ps</h3><h4 id="Files"><a href="#Files" class="headerlink" title="Files"></a>Files</h4><p><code>TIME</code>: the cumulated CPU time in [DD-]hh:mm:ss format (time&#x3D;TIME)</p><table><thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>value &amp; means</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><code>TIME</code></td><td><code>1-18:09:38</code> means “1 day, 18 hours, 9 minutes and 38 seconds”</td></tr></tbody></table><h2 id="Reference"><a href="#Reference" class="headerlink" title="Reference"></a>Reference</h2><p><a href="https://serverfault.com/questions/138427/what-does-virtual-memory-size-in-top-mean">what-does-virtual-memory-size-in-top-mean</a></p>]]></content>
      
      
